newsitem.title: INDONESIA: Jakarta call money stable at 13.0/14.0 percent.
newsitem.headline: Jakarta call money stable at 13.0/14.0 percent.

text.p: Jakarta call money was stable at 13.0/14.0 percent on Tuesday morning on sufficient liquidity supply, dealers said.
They said liquidity appeared to be well supplied in the morning, but short-dated swap rates remained expensive.
One foreign bank dealer said fears that rupiah supply could be tight on Friday following similar conditions on the last three Fridays kept operators cautious.
Overnight swap was at 0.55/0.65 and tom/next at 0.63/0.70.
The average overnight interbank rate on Tuesday was 13.95 percent, compared with 15.72 percent on Monday.
